  "text": "to the desired concentration and added onto preseeded OP50 E. coli bacteriumcontaining nematode growth medium (NGM) plates. The plates were dried uncovered in the hood for at least 1 h before seeding the worms. Synchronized L1-stage animals were dropped onto the drug-containing plates and scored later. For drug resistance assays synchronized L1 larval stage animals of the appropriate genotype were fed with either control RNAi or with RNAi clones targeting bile acid biosynthetic pathways until they reached day 2 of adulthood. Subsequently, the RNAi-treated animals were egg-prepped to obtain synchronized L1 larvae. About 100 L1 larvae were added to the plates containing G418. 100 nM [CITATION_1] -dafachronic acid or (25S)-7 -dafachronic acid from Cayman Chemical was used in the daf-12 experiments. In the purified bile experiments, bile from bovine and ovine (mixed bile acids), chenodeoxycholic acids, glycochenodeoxycholic acid, glycocholic acid, taurocholic acid, lithocholic acid and taurochenodeoxycholic acid from Sigma were diluted in M9 to the desired concentration (100 µM) and added onto preseeded OP50 E. coli bacterium-containing NGM plates. The plates were dried uncovered in the hood for at least 1 h before seeding the worms.",
